---
import { Code } from "astro:components";
import BlogLayout from "../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/docs/CodeBlock.astro";
import { brandShikiTheme } from "../../config/code-theme.mjs";

const editTs = `export const User = defineTable("user", {
  name: s.string(),
  email: s.string().email(),
  role: s.enum(["admin", "member", "owner"]),
  lastSeen: s.datetime().optional(),
});`;

const migrationSurql = `-- migrations/0002_user.surql
ALTER FIELD role ON TABLE user TYPE "admin" | "member" | "owner";
DEFINE FIELD lastSeen ON TABLE user TYPE option<datetime>;`;
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Incremental migrations: ALTER, not rip-and-replace"
  description="The CLI now diffs into clause-level ALTER statements that touch only what changed."
  glow={true}
>
  <a class="back" href="/blog">&larr; Blog</a>

  <div class="meta">
    <span class="tag">RELEASE</span>
    <span class="date">2026-06-10 &middot; 8 min read</span>
  </div>
  <h1 class="title">Incremental migrations: ALTER, not rip-and-replace</h1>

  <div class="author">
    <span class="avatar">MS</span>
    <span class="ainfo">
      <span class="an">Manuel Sanchez</span>
      <span class="ar">Maintainer &middot; SurrealDB Ambassador</span>
    </span>
  </div>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <div class="article doc-prose">
    <p class="lead">
      Until now, applying a schema change meant <code>OVERWRITE</code>-ing the
      whole table. That works, but it is a blunt instrument: it rewrites clauses
      you never touched and makes every diff look total. The new CLI does the
      careful thing instead.
    </p>

    <p>
      <code>sc gen</code> now diffs your schema into clause-level
      <code>ALTER TABLE</code> and <code>ALTER FIELD</code> statements (and
      <code>REMOVE</code> + <code>DEFINE</code> for indexes). Migrations touch
      only what changed and preserve everything they do not mention. Edit one
      field type and you get one <code>ALTER FIELD</code>, not a rewritten table.
    </p>

    <h2>Try it</h2>
    <p>
      Change the schema (an enum value plus a new optional field), and the
      generator emits the migration below.
    </p>

    <CodeBlock title="user.ts" lang="ts">
      <Code code={editTs} lang="ts" theme={brandShikiTheme} />
    </CodeBlock>

    <CodeBlock title="Generated migration" lang="surql">
      <Code code={migrationSurql} lang="sql" theme={brandShikiTheme} />
    </CodeBlock>

    <blockquote class="pull">
      Safe migrations, not rip-and-replace — and every up/down round-trips on
      real SurrealDB.
    </blockquote>

    <p>
      Pair this with <code>sc check</code>, which replays every migration from
      zero on a throwaway database and confirms it reproduces your declared
      schema. Together they catch the bug every DDL tool has but few detect: a
      migration that no longer builds the schema it claims to.
    </p>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>

<style>
  .back {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-3);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--color-soft);
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-purple) 15%, transparent);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }
  .date {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-3);
  }
  .title {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 2vw, 2.875rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .author {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .avatar {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff;
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--color-purple),
      var(--color-pink)
    );
  }
  .ainfo {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .an {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .ar {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-3);
  }
  .rule {
    border: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .article .lead {
    font-size: 1.1875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .pull {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-purple);
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
</style>
